# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1923-chicago-american-giants-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1920-chicago-american-giants-season] The **1920 Chicago American Giants baseball team** represented the Chicago American Giants in the Negro National League (NNL) during the 1920 baseball season.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1920-chicago-american-giants-season] The team compiled a 51–19–2 record (45–15–2 in NNL games) and won the first NNL championship.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1920-chicago-american-giants-season] Rube Foster was the team's owner and manager.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1920-chicago-american-giants-season] The team played its home games at Schorling Park in Chicago.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1921-chicago-american-giants-season] The **1921 Chicago American Giants baseball team** represented the Chicago American Giants in the Negro National League (NNL) during the 1920 baseball season.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1921-chicago-american-giants-season] The team compiled a 55–28–4 record (44–22–2 against NNL opponents) and won the NNL pennant.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1922-chicago-american-giants-season] The **1922 Chicago American Giants baseball team** represented the Chicago American Giants in the Negro National League (NNL) during the 1922 baseball season.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1922-chicago-american-giants-season] The team compiled a 46–30–1 record (38–23–1 in NNL games) and won the NNL pennant for the third consecutive season.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-boston-braves-season] The **1923 Boston Braves season** was the 53rd season of the franchise.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-boston-red-sox-season] The **1923 Boston Red Sox season** was the 23rd season in the franchise's Major League Baseball history.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-boston-red-sox-season] The Red Sox finished last in the eight-team American League (AL) with a record of 61 wins and 91 losses, 37 games behind the New York Yankees, who went on to win the 1923 World Series.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-brooklyn-robins-season] A poor season found the **1923 Brooklyn Robins** in sixth place once more.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-chicago-american-giants-season] The **1923 Chicago American Giants baseball team** represented the Chicago American Giants in the Negro National League (NNL) during the 1923 baseball season.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-chicago-american-giants-season] The team compiled a 48–29–1 record (42–29 in NNL games) and finished in second place in the NNL.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-chicago-american-giants-season] The independent Cleveland Tate Stars returned to the NNL as an associate member to finish the Tigers' schedule.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-chicago-american-giants-season] The team was not considered a full member of the NNL.
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-chicago-cubs-season] The **1923 Chicago Cubs season** was the 52nd season of the Chicago Cubs franchise, the 48th in the National League and the eighth at Wrigley Field (then known as "Cubs Park").
[src:1923-chicago-american-giants-season/1923-chicago-cubs-season] The Cubs finished fourth in the National League with a record of 83–71.
